trans-unit.source: Represents a collection of <see cref="T:System.Windows.Forms.TreeNode" /> objects.
trans-unit.target: Representa una colección de objetos <see cref="T:System.Windows.Forms.TreeNode" />.

trans-unit.source: The <xref:System.Windows.Forms.TreeNodeCollection.Add%2A>, <xref:System.Windows.Forms.TreeNodeCollection.Remove%2A>, and <xref:System.Windows.Forms.TreeNodeCollection.RemoveAt%2A> methods enable you to add and remove individual tree nodes from the collection.
trans-unit.target: El <xref:System.Windows.Forms.TreeNodeCollection.Add%2A>, <xref:System.Windows.Forms.TreeNodeCollection.Remove%2A>, y <xref:System.Windows.Forms.TreeNodeCollection.RemoveAt%2A> métodos permiten agregar y quitar nodos de árbol individuales de la colección.

trans-unit.source: Enumerating the collection and removing nodes is not supported.
trans-unit.target: No se admiten la enumeración de la colección y quitar nodos.

trans-unit.source: You can also use the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.TreeNodeCollection.AddRange%2A> or <xref:System.Windows.Forms.TreeNodeCollection.Clear%2A> methods to add or remove all the tree nodes from the collection.
trans-unit.target: También puede usar el <xref:System.Windows.Forms.TreeNodeCollection.AddRange%2A> o <xref:System.Windows.Forms.TreeNodeCollection.Clear%2A> métodos para agregar o quitar todos los nodos de árbol de la colección.

trans-unit.source: Classes cannot inherit from the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.TreeNodeCollection> class.
trans-unit.target: Las clases no se pueden heredar de la <xref:System.Windows.Forms.TreeNodeCollection> clase.

trans-unit.target: En el ejemplo de código siguiente se muestra la información del cliente en un <xref:System.Windows.Forms.TreeView> control.

trans-unit.source: The root tree nodes display customer names, and the child tree nodes display the order numbers assigned to each customer.

trans-unit.source: In this example, 1,000 customers are displayed with 15 orders each.
trans-unit.target: En este ejemplo, se muestran 1.000 clientes con 15 pedidos.

trans-unit.source: This example requires that you have created a <xref:System.Windows.Forms.TreeView> and a <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Button> on a <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Form>.
trans-unit.target: Este ejemplo requiere que se haya creado un <xref:System.Windows.Forms.TreeView> y un <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Button> en un <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Form>.

trans-unit.source: The first <xref:System.Windows.Forms.TreeNode> in your <xref:System.Windows.Forms.TreeView> should have a text property of "Node0."
trans-unit.target: La primera <xref:System.Windows.Forms.TreeNode> en su <xref:System.Windows.Forms.TreeView> deben tener una propiedad de texto de "Node0".

trans-unit.source: The <paramref name="index" /> value is less than 0 or is greater than the number of tree nodes in the collection.
trans-unit.target: El valor de <paramref name="index" /> es menor que 0 o mayor que el número de nodos de árbol de la colección.

trans-unit.source: The name of the <see cref="T:System.Windows.Forms.TreeNode" /> to retrieve from the collection.
trans-unit.target: Nombre del control <see cref="T:System.Windows.Forms.TreeNode" /> que se va a recuperar de la colección.

trans-unit.source: Gets the tree node with the specified key from the collection.
trans-unit.target: Obtiene el nodo de árbol con la clave especificada de la colección.

trans-unit.source: The <see cref="T:System.Windows.Forms.TreeNode" /> with the specified key.
trans-unit.target: El objeto <see cref="T:System.Windows.Forms.TreeNode" /> con la clave especificada.

trans-unit.source: The <xref:System.Windows.Forms.TreeNode.Name%2A> property corresponds to the key for a <xref:System.Windows.Forms.TreeNode> in the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.TreeNodeCollection>.
trans-unit.target: El <xref:System.Windows.Forms.TreeNode.Name%2A> propiedad se corresponde con la clave para un <xref:System.Windows.Forms.TreeNode> en el <xref:System.Windows.Forms.TreeNodeCollection>.

trans-unit.source: The key comparison is not case-sensitive.
trans-unit.target: La comparación de claves no distingue mayúsculas de minúsculas.

trans-unit.source: If the `key` parameter is `null` or an empty string, the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.TreeNodeCollection.Item%2A> property returns `null`.
trans-unit.target: Si el `key` parámetro es `null` o una cadena vacía, el <xref:System.Windows.Forms.TreeNodeCollection.Item%2A> propiedad devuelve `null`.

trans-unit.source: The <see cref="T:System.Windows.Forms.TreeNode" /> to remove.
trans-unit.target: <see cref="T:System.Windows.Forms.TreeNode" /> que se va a quitar.

trans-unit.source: Removes the specified tree node from the tree node collection.
trans-unit.target: Quita el nodo de árbol especificado de la colección de nodos de árbol.

trans-unit.source: When a <xref:System.Windows.Forms.TreeNode> is removed from the tree node collection, all subsequent tree nodes are moved up one position in the collection.
trans-unit.target: Cuando un <xref:System.Windows.Forms.TreeNode> se quita de la colección de nodos de árbol, todos los árboles posteriores nodos se mueven hacia arriba una posición en la colección.

trans-unit.source: You can also remove a <xref:System.Windows.Forms.TreeNode> that you previously added by using the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.TreeNodeCollection.RemoveAt%2A> or <xref:System.Windows.Forms.TreeNodeCollection.Clear%2A> methods.
trans-unit.target: También puede quitar un <xref:System.Windows.Forms.TreeNode> que agregó anteriormente mediante el uso de la <xref:System.Windows.Forms.TreeNodeCollection.RemoveAt%2A> o <xref:System.Windows.Forms.TreeNodeCollection.Clear%2A> métodos.

trans-unit.source: Enumerating the collection and removing nodes is not supported.
trans-unit.target: No se admiten la enumeración de la colección y quitar nodos.

trans-unit.source: To add new <xref:System.Windows.Forms.TreeNode> objects to the collection, use the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.TreeNodeCollection.Add%2A>, <xref:System.Windows.Forms.TreeNodeCollection.AddRange%2A>, or <xref:System.Windows.Forms.TreeNodeCollection.Insert%2A> methods.
trans-unit.target: Para agregar nuevos <xref:System.Windows.Forms.TreeNode> objetos a la colección, utilice el <xref:System.Windows.Forms.TreeNodeCollection.Add%2A>, <xref:System.Windows.Forms.TreeNodeCollection.AddRange%2A>, o <xref:System.Windows.Forms.TreeNodeCollection.Insert%2A> métodos.

trans-unit.source: The following code example removes the selected tree node from one <xref:System.Windows.Forms.TreeView> and adds it to another if both tree node collections are not read-only.
trans-unit.target: En el ejemplo de código siguiente se quita el nodo de árbol seleccionado de uno <xref:System.Windows.Forms.TreeView> y lo agrega a otro si ambas colecciones de nodos de árbol no son de solo lectura.

trans-unit.source: When a <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Button> is clicked, the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.TreeNode> represented by the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.TreeView.SelectedNode%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> property is deleted from one <xref:System.Windows.Forms.TreeView> using the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.TreeNodeCollection.Remove%2A> method and added to the other <xref:System.Windows.Forms.TreeView> using the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.TreeNodeCollection.Insert%2A> method.

trans-unit.source: This example requires that you have a <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Form> that contains two <xref:System.Windows.Forms.TreeView> controls and a <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Button>.
trans-unit.target: Este ejemplo requiere que haya un <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Form> que contiene dos <xref:System.Windows.Forms.TreeView> controles y <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Button>.

trans-unit.target: El <xref:System.Windows.Forms.TreeView> controles deben denominarse `treeView1` y `treeView2`.
